Path: godot/getting_started/first_3d_game/04.mob_scene.rst
Summary: This section describes the process of creating the Mob scene in Godot, including setting up the node structure, adding the 3D model, and configuring the collision shape.
Create a new scene with a CharacterBody3D node as the root, named "Mob".
Add a Node3D child node named "Pivot".
Drag and drop the "mob.glb" file from the FileSystem dock onto the "Pivot" node to add the monster's 3D model.
Rename the newly created "mob" node to "Character".
Add a CollisionShape3D as a child node to the "Mob" root node.
In the Inspector, assign a BoxShape3D to the Shape property of the CollisionShape3D.
Adjust the size of the BoxShape3D interactively to better fit the 3D model. The box should touch the floor and be slightly thinner than the model.
Key Rule: Collision shapes do not need to perfectly match the 3D model; their size and form should be dictated by how the game feels during testing to ensure fair gameplay.
---CHUNK---
